oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Masonic Building Collapse, Front Exterior, 1949
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Black and white photograph of the Masonic Building in downtown Clarksville after the building collapsed. The inside of the Masonic Building is exposed after the front of the building fell during the second stage of the collapse. The Watkins Auto Parts storefront is also visible.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Building failures; Freemasonry--Lodges; Building, Brick; Advertising; Storefronts;
